# WaveX UI System Guide

## Screen Management
The UI system in [script.js](mdc:script.js) manages multiple screens:

### Screen Structure
- **`#screen-main`**: Main menu with navigation buttons
- **`#screen-play`**: Song selection and difficulty filtering
- **`#screen-game`**: Active gameplay canvas and HUD
- **`#screen-editor`**: Chart creation and editing interface
- **`#screen-community`**: Community charts browser
- **`#screen-profile`**: User profile and statistics
- **`#screen-options`**: Game settings and preferences

### Screen Navigation
- **`Screens.go(screenId)`**: Switch between screens
- **`Screens.active`**: Currently active screen
- **Screen transitions**: Smooth animations between states

## Modal System
### Modal Components
- **Pause Modal**: Resume, restart, and quit options
- **Results Modal**: Score display, rank, XP rewards
- **Admin Panel Modal**: Login and song management

### Modal Styling
```css
.modal {
  position: fixed;
  inset: 0;
  z-index: 1000;
  backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
}
```

## Game HUD Elements
### Canvas Rendering
- **Game Canvas**: Main gameplay area with notes and lanes
- **Timeline Canvas**: Editor timeline visualization
- **Responsive Sizing**: Automatic canvas resizing on window changes

### HUD Components
- **Score Display**: Current score and combo
- **Health Bar**: Visual health indicator (if enabled)
- **Accuracy**: Hit percentage and judgment breakdown
- **Progress Bar**: Song progress indicator

## Styling System
### CSS Architecture
The [style.css](mdc:style.css) file implements:

### Color Scheme
- **Primary**: Dark futuristic theme (#121427)
- **Accents**: Neon blue (#00E5FF), purple (#8B5CF6), pink (#EC4899)
- **Text**: White (#FFFFFF) with various opacity levels
- **Borders**: Subtle white borders with transparency

### Component Styling
- **Buttons**: Neon glow effects with hover states
- **Cards**: Glassmorphism with backdrop blur
- **Inputs**: Dark theme with focus highlights
- **Animations**: Smooth transitions and hover effects

### Responsive Design
- **Mobile First**: Base styles for mobile devices
- **Breakpoints**: Responsive adjustments for larger screens
- **Touch Friendly**: Appropriate sizing for mobile interaction

## UI Components

### Song Cards
- **Artwork Display**: Song cover images with fallbacks
- **Metadata**: Title, artist, difficulty, and rating
- **Actions**: Play, download, and rate buttons

### Navigation
- **Main Menu**: Large, accessible navigation buttons
- **Breadcrumbs**: Clear navigation hierarchy
- **Search/Filter**: Song search and difficulty filtering

### Forms and Inputs
- **Chart Editor**: Title, artist, difficulty inputs
- **File Upload**: MP3 and artwork file selection
- **Settings**: Volume sliders, toggle switches

## Animation System
### CSS Animations
- **Keyframes**: Smooth transitions and effects
- **Transforms**: Scale, rotate, and translate animations
- **Transitions**: Hover states and screen changes

### JavaScript Animations
- **Particle Effects**: Background animations
- **Note Animations**: Hit effects and lane highlights
- **UI Transitions**: Smooth screen and modal changes

## Accessibility Features
- **Keyboard Navigation**: Full keyboard support
- **Screen Reader**: Semantic HTML structure
- **Color Contrast**: High contrast for readability
- **Focus Management**: Clear focus indicators
